From 1a0006000000000000000000000000000000ob06 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: OpenBook Maintainers <goodhackersolutions@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 8 Jun 2026 00:00:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] features: package the OpenBook hardening layer + native hosts

SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0

Adds the OpenBook-installed files to the packaging manifest so `mach package`
ships them. EVERY OpenBook line below is an ADDITION (+): none of these paths
exist in upstream Firefox, so a patch that listed them as context could never
apply — and worse, a package built without them would silently lack the
telemetry-off/policy layer (a release-blocking fail-open). package.sh verifies
the files in dist/ before packaging AND the packaged archive must contain them.

  - defaults/pref/autoconfig.js + openbook.cfg: the AutoConfig hardening layer
    (installed into dist by build/scripts/install-config.sh after the build).
  - distribution/policies.json: the enterprise-policy layer.
  - distribution/extensions/<id>.xpi: the three bundled first-party extensions,
    installed via Mozilla's supported distribution-extensions mechanism (no
    source patch needed to make Firefox load them — this replaces the earlier
    speculative builtinExtensions.json patch, which targeted a file that does
    not exist upstream). The XPIs are built by package-components.sh and staged
    into dist/distribution/extensions/ before `mach package` on the build host.
  - native-messaging host manifests + vault host binary (linux packaging v1;
    macOS/Windows native-messaging paths differ and land with their packaging
    recipes).

The browser READS and validates a native-host manifest's allowed_extensions but
does NOT install or manage the host -- its security model is that of a native
application (docs/OpenBook-Browser-Build-Plan.md §1). Therefore the manifest and
the host binary MUST be installed by OS packaging, root-owned and NOT
user-writable. A user-writable native-host manifest or binary is a local
privilege-escalation hole and is a RELEASE BLOCKER (§11). Each manifest's
allowed_extensions binds it to its first-party extension ID
(vault_host <-> vault-ui@openbook.browser;
 vpn_helper <-> proxy-manager@openbook.browser).

NOTE: hunk offsets are reconciled against the real firefox-145.0.2 tree by the
rebase step (docs/RELEASE-CHECKLIST.md §3); context anchors are the
long-standing `[Browser Chrome Files]` section markers and apply-patches.sh
runs patch with --fuzz=0 (exact context, offsets allowed).
---
 browser/installer/package-manifest.in | 22 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 22 insertions(+)

diff --git a/browser/installer/package-manifest.in b/browser/installer/package-manifest.in
index bbbbbbb..ccccccc 100644
--- a/browser/installer/package-manifest.in
+++ b/browser/installer/package-manifest.in
@@ -60,2 +60,24 @@
 ; [Browser Chrome Files]
+; --- OpenBook hardening layer (Build Plan §4/§11) ---------------------------
+; Installed into dist by build/scripts/install-config.sh after the build; the
+; package MUST carry them or the shipped browser has no telemetry-off layer.
+@RESPATH@/defaults/pref/autoconfig.js
+@BINPATH@/openbook.cfg
+@RESPATH@/distribution/policies.json
+; Bundled first-party extensions via the distribution mechanism (auto-installed
+; on first run; allowlisted by ExtensionSettings in policies.json).
+@RESPATH@/distribution/extensions/vault-ui@openbook.browser.xpi
+@RESPATH@/distribution/extensions/proxy-manager@openbook.browser.xpi
+@RESPATH@/distribution/extensions/ai-sidebar@openbook.browser.xpi
+; OpenBook native-messaging host manifests + binary (linux v1; macOS/Windows
+; land with their per-OS packaging recipes). Installed by OS packaging
+; root-owned, NOT user-writable (§11); post-install fixes ownership to
+; root:root and mode (manifests 0644, binary 0755). The browser only validates
+; allowed_extensions; it never manages the host itself.
+#ifdef XP_LINUX
+@RESPATH@/native-messaging-hosts/org.openbook.vault_host.json
+@RESPATH@/native-messaging-hosts/org.openbook.vpn_helper.json
+@BINPATH@/openbook-vault-host
+#endif
+; --- end OpenBook ------------------------------------------------------------
 @RESPATH@/browser/chrome.manifest
